 				Ping Pong

Properties and methods used from Turtle library:

	1. M.turtle.Screen() - Creates a blank window.
	2. P.title() - Sets titles for the window
	3. P.bgcolor() - Sets bgcolor.
	4. P.setup() - It takes 2 args(width & height)
	5. P.tracer() - With arg as 0 enables manual updating
	6. P.update() - Updates window.
	7. M.turtle.Turtle() - Creates a turtle object.
	8. p.speed() - Adjusts the speed of the animation 0 being fastest.
	9. P.shape() - Declares predefined shapes.
	10. P.color() - Adjusts the color
	11. P.penup() - Disables writing.
	12. P.goto() - Specifies coordinates for turtle object.
	13. P.shapesize() - Stretches shape with args stretch_wid and stretch_len
	14. P.ycor() - Returns Y cordinates of turtle object.
	15. P.sety(y) - Sets Y cor for turtle obj.
	16. P.listen() - Turtle library starts listening for key presses.
	17 P.onkeypress(function(), key) - Listens for keypress and calls a function


Steps:
__________

	1. Setup the game window
	2. Create a game loop
	3. Create paddles
	4. Create the ball
	5. Gives movement to the paddles
	6. Give ball movement